<br>
1) Allow monks to use block, dodge and riposte from the rear and not have FD break when a mob casts on you FD. Allow the spells to hit, but not cause all the mobs to continue agro unless the FD failed in the first place.<br>
<br>
or <br>
<br>
2) Increase monks offense to the point they are the number one melee damage dealer. If monks are going to be last in defense, then first in offence is balanced. Give monks something like critical kicks that hit for similar damage as rogue back stab as long as the mob is kicked from behind. Couple this with AA's to make off hand weapons hit as often and with the same damage bonuses as the primary hand. Or give monks an AA skill similar to rangers that allow monks to use thrown weapons for similar damage as rangers bows. Make the thrown weapons needed blacksmithable with purchased components. Make these weapons do good damage during normal fighting as well. There is no reason a thrown hammer or javelin shouldn't do as much damage a any arrow. They could also add bags to hold these weapons like quivers for arrows.<br>
<br>
Personally, I would like things the way they were, but it is obvious that most other people at least percieve monks as too powerful. I have only gotten two simpathy comments from my own guild and many people are outright gloating over it (mostly warriors, but a couple rogues as well.) Of course I hear we are supposed to be damage dealers, not tanks, melees shouldn't be able to solo and verrant never meant for monks to pull. But it is amazing to me that our monks rarely if ever get put into one of the bard hasted DPS groups at raids. It seems they are all full of rogues and rangers. I stopped logging raids after seeing rogues do 2x the damage of the monks and rangers going 4-6x the damage consistantly on the main boss mobs. One of our rangers was upset with himself because he only did 20k damage in a less than 2 minute fight tonight. Rogue and ranger skills are at least comparable to monk skills, so it is imbalanced that they have better offence and defence<br>
<br>
I think the run5 is also a good idea and makes sense reguardless of the current nerf. <p>Clawr 54th Monk    
